{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846051607,"sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","part":{"id":"prt_d78ac03ea001asC4jy0e365hdD","messageID":"msg_d78abe649001ZycW4wsRnC5AVF","sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ec2ab874c9cf4f5ea46dfd71","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Overview\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **AR** | AR-008 |\n| **Module** | pkg/workloadmanager |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S |\n| **Status** | Open |\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module manages Sandboxes (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter instances). Currently, expiration logic exists in `expiration.go` to determine if a Sandbox is expired based on TTL, idle timeout, max lifetime, and stale state. However, there is no scheduled background process to automatically detect and clean up expired sandboxes.\n\nThis delta adds a scheduled GC (Garbage Collection) mechanism to periodically scan and clean up expired Sandboxes.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Scheduled GC Background Worker\n\n**GIVEN** a WorkloadManager instance with GC enabled\n**WHEN** the server starts\n**THEN** a background goroutine should start that periodically checks for expired Sandboxes\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n1. **GC Worker Starts on Server Init**\n   - GIVEN a WorkloadManager with DefaultGCInterval (5 minutes) configured\n   - WHEN the workloadmanager service starts\n   - THEN a background goroutine should begin running with a ticker interval of 5 minutes\n\n2. **GC Worker Can Be Disabled**\n   - GIVEN a WorkloadManager with GCEnabled set to false\n   - WHEN the workloadmanager service starts\n   - THEN no background GC goroutine should be started\n\n3. **GC Interval Is Configurable**\n   - GIVEN a WorkloadManager with GCInterval set to 10 minutes\n   - WHEN the background GC goroutine runs\n   - THEN the ticker should fire every 10 minutes\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Expired Sandbox Detection\n\n**GIVEN** the GC worker is running and scans a namespace\n**WHEN** it finds a Sandbox where `isExpired(sandbox)` returns true\n**THEN** that Sandbox should be marked for deletion\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n1. **Detect TTL-Expired Sandbox**\n   - GIVEN a Sandbox with CreatedAt more than 8 hours ago and no ExpiresAt set\n   - WHEN the GC worker runs isExpired check\n   - THEN the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n2. **Detect Idle-Timeout Expired Sandbox**\n   - GIVEN a Sandbox with LastActivityAt more than 15 minutes ago\n   - WHEN the GC worker runs isExpired check\n   - THEN the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n3. **Detect Max-Lifetime Expired Sandbox**\n   - GIVEN a Sandbox with CreatedAt more than 24 hours ago\n   - WHEN the GC worker runs isExpired check\n   - THEN the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n4. **Detect Stale-State Sandbox**\n   - GIVEN a Sandbox in state \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" with CreatedAt more than 1 hour ago\n   - WHEN the GC worker runs isExpired check\n   - THEN the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: Expired Sandbox Cleanup\n\n**GIVEN** an expired Sandbox identified by the GC worker\n**WHEN** the cleanup process begins\n**THEN** the Sandbox should be deleted and its orphaned resources cleaned up\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n1. **Graceful Deletion with Default Grace Period**\n   - GIVEN an expired Sandbox\n   - WHEN the GC worker triggers deletion with default grace period\n   - THEN the Sandbox should be deleted with a 30-second grace period\n   - AND associated Services, ConfigMaps, and PVCs should be cleaned up\n\n2. **Force Deletion for Stale Sandbox**\n   - GIVEN a Sandbox in stale state (Unknown/Failed) for more than threshold\n   - WHEN the GC worker triggers deletion\n   - THEN the Sandbox should be force-deleted (GracePeriodSeconds=0)\n\n3. **Orphaned Resource Cleanup**\n   - GIVEN an expired Sandbox that had created K8s resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n   - WHEN the cleanup runs\n   - THEN all owned resources should be deleted\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: GC Metrics and Logging\n\n**GIVEN** the GC worker running\n**WHEN** it scans and cleans up sandboxes\n**THEN** it should log actions and expose metrics\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n1. **Log GC Cycle**\n   - GIVEN the GC worker running\n   - WHEN a GC cycle completes\n   - THEN it should log the number of sandboxes scanned and cleaned\n\n2. **Log Cleanup Details**\n   - GIVEN an expired Sandbox being cleaned up\n   - WHEN cleanup completes\n   - THEN it should log which resources were cleaned\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe following configuration options should be available:\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| GCEnabled | bool | true | Enable/disable GC background worker |\n| GCInterval | time.Duration | 5m | Interval between GC cycles |\n| GCBatchSize | int | 50 | Max sandboxes to process per cycle |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `expiration.go` - Existing expiration detection logic\n- `cleanup.go` - Existing resource cleanup logic\n- Uses client-go for K8s operations (as specified in base specs)\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\nNew file: `pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go` - GC worker implementation\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] GC background worker starts automatically when workloadmanager starts\n- [ ] GC can be disabled via configuration\n- [ ] GC interval is configurable\n- [ ] All four expiration types (TTL, idle, max lifetime, stale) are detected\n- [ ] Expired sandboxes are deleted with appropriate grace period\n- [ ] Orphaned K8s resources are cleaned up after sandbox deletion\n- [ ] GC actions are logged","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775846051599,"end":1775846051604}}}}
