{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846063211,"sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","part":{"id":"prt_d78ac7871001xkXNw8x8UZwuRL","messageID":"msg_d78ac641400101vO1LlUjok3GJ","sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_927fda3572944e83bb9df2d8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) timer-based cleanup mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-008\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: - **Base Spec**: (TBD)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenarios\n18: \n19: (TBD)\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Acceptance Criteria\n24: \n25: (TBD)\n\n(End of file - total 25 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) timer-based cleanup mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-008\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Spec**: (TBD)\n\n---\n\n## Scenarios\n\n(TBD)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775846063194,"end":1775846063209}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775846063234,"sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","part":{"id":"prt_d78ac7c6a001ibxgFXhgZTtCru","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78ac641400101vO1LlUjok3GJ","sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":39821,"input":3798,"output":249,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":35774}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775846064889,"sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","part":{"id":"prt_d78ac82f60016KhPzlvJDIJf3r","messageID":"msg_d78ac7c9f001VGszsFA6ZsqmO5","sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846088638,"sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","part":{"id":"prt_d78ac860b001kQ7D2gnXsx9Vhd","messageID":"msg_d78ac7c9f001VGszsFA6ZsqmO5","sessionID":"ses_287548ae9ffe5DruKIg28I3WMR","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_fb19db863edf4d7fb4d2295c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) timer-based cleanup mechanism in `pkg/workloadmanager`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-008\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Spec**: client-go library for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe workloadmanager module manages Sandboxes (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter instances). Currently, expiration logic exists in `expiration.go` to determine if a Sandbox is expired based on:\n- TTL (Time To Live): 8 hours default\n- Idle timeout: 15 minutes default  \n- Max lifetime: 24 hours default\n- Stale state: Unknown/Failed state for more than 1 hour\n\nThe cleanup logic in `cleanup.go` handles removal of orphaned Kubernetes resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs).\n\nHowever, there is no scheduled background process to automatically detect and clean up expired sandboxes. This delta adds a scheduled GC mechanism.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: GC Worker Lifecycle\n\n### Scenario: GC worker starts on server initialization\n\n**GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with default GC configuration (GCEnabled=true, GCInterval=5m)\n**WHEN** the workloadmanager service starts\n**THEN** a background goroutine should start running with a ticker that fires every 5 minutes\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: GC worker can be disabled via configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with GCEnabled set to false\n**WHEN** the workloadmanager service starts\n**THEN** no background GC goroutine should be started\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: GC interval is configurable\n\n**GIVEN** a WorkloadManager with GCInterval set to 10 minutes\n**WHEN** the background GC goroutine runs\n**THEN** the ticker should fire every 10 minutes\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: GC worker stops gracefully on shutdown\n\n**GIVEN** a running GC background goroutine\n**WHEN** the WorkloadManager's Close() method is called\n**THEN** the GC goroutine should stop and not process any more sandboxes\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Expired Sandbox Detection\n\n### Scenario: Detect TTL-expired sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** a Sandbox with CreatedAt time more than 8 hours ago and no ExpiresAt set\n**WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByTTL)\n**THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: Detect idle-timeout expired sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** a Sandbox with LastActivityAt more than 15 minutes ago\n**WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByIdleTimeout)\n**THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: Detect max-lifetime expired sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** a Sandbox with CreatedAt more than 24 hours ago\n**WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByMaxLifetime)\n**THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: Detect stale-state sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** a Sandbox in state \"Unknown\" or \"Failed\" with CreatedAt more than 1 hour ago\n**WHEN** the GC worker runs the isExpired check (expiration.go:isExpiredByStaleState)\n**THEN** the Sandbox should be identified as expired\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Expired Sandbox Cleanup\n\n### Scenario: Delete expired sandbox with default grace period\n\n**GIVEN** an expired Sandbox\n**WHEN** the GC worker triggers deletion\n**THEN** the Sandbox should be deleted with a 30-second grace period (default from expiration.go:CalculateGracePeriod)\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: Force delete stale sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** a Sandbox in stale state (Unknown/Failed) for more than 1 hour\n**WHEN** the GC worker triggers deletion\n**THEN** the Sandbox should be force-deleted with GracePeriodSeconds=0\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: Clean up orphaned Kubernetes resources\n\n**GIVEN** an expired Sandbox that created K8s resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs)\n**WHEN** the cleanup process runs (using cleanup.go:CleanupAllResources)\n**THEN** all owned Services, ConfigMaps, and PVCs should be deleted\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: Skip deletion of retained PVCs\n\n**GIVEN** an expired Sandbox with an owned PVC backed by a PersistentVolume with ReclaimPolicy=Retain\n**WHEN** the cleanup process attempts to delete the PVC\n**THEN** the PVC should be skipped and retained\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: GC Metrics and Logging\n\n### Scenario: Log GC cycle results\n\n**GIVEN** the GC worker running\n**WHEN** a GC cycle completes\n**THEN** it should log the number of sandboxes scanned and the number cleaned\n\n---\n\n### Scenario: Log cleanup details per sandbox\n\n**GIVEN** an expired Sandbox being cleaned up\n**WHEN** cleanup completes\n**THEN** it should log which resources were cleaned (Service/ConfigMap/PVC names)\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe following configuration options should be available:\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| GCEnabled | bool | true | Enable/disable GC background worker |\n| GCInterval | time.Duration | 5m | Interval between GC cycles |\n| GCBatchSize | int | 50 | Max sandboxes to process per cycle |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `expiration.go` - Existing expiration detection logic (isExpired, isExpiredByTTL, isExpiredByIdleTimeout, etc.)\n- `cleanup.go` - Existing resource cleanup logic (CleanupManager)\n- Uses client-go for K8s operations\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\nNew file to create: `pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go`\n\nThe GC worker should:\n1. Accept a context and stop channel for graceful shutdown\n2. Use a time.Ticker for periodic execution\n3. Call ListSandboxes to get all sandboxes\n4. Filter expired ones using existing isExpired() function\n5. Delete expired sandboxes via WorkloadManager\n6. Clean up orphaned resources using CleanupManager\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] GC background worker starts automatically when workloadmanager starts (if GCEnabled=true)\n- [ ] GC can be disabled via configuration (GCEnabled=false)\n- [ ] GC interval is configurable (default 5 minutes)\n- [ ] GC worker stops gracefully on WorkloadManager Close()\n- [ ] All four expiration types (TTL, idle, max lifetime, stale) are correctly detected\n- [ ] Expired sandboxes are deleted with appropriate grace period\n- [ ] Force deletion (GracePeriodSeconds=0) is used for stale sandboxes\n- [ ] Orphaned K8s resources (Services, ConfigMaps, PVCs) are cleaned up\n- [ ] PVCs with Retain policy are skipped during cleanup\n- [ ] GC cycle results are logged (scanned count, cleaned count)\n- [ ] Cleanup details are logged per sandbox","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/service_test.go\">\nERROR [127:9] cannot use &testWorkloadManager{…} (value of type *testWorkloadManager) as WorkloadManager value in return statement: *testWorkloadManager does not implement WorkloadManager (missing method DeleteSandbox)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go\">\nERROR [33:22] cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime value in assignment: need type assertion\nERROR [40:9] invalid operation: ob